						<summary>

						<p>On a stone in the Nāgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Undated. Palaeographically assignable to 10th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>Registers a grant of 20 <hi rend="italic">maṟuturu</hi> of land to god Takshakēśvarabhaṭāra of Nariyanūru made by the Three Hundred <hi rend="italic">(munnūṟṟuvuru).</hi> Refers to a person named Nāga-Chaṇḍasvāmi-Tippaṇa-Pōtiya of Sāṁkhya[?]-<hi rend="italic">gōtra</hi> as the builder of the temple (?) and to the place as Kapila-<hi rend="italic">maṭham.</hi> It is not clear whether Pōtiya was the priest of the temple of Takshakēśvara. The <hi rend="italic">gōtra</hi> might be Sāṅkhyāyana.</p>						

						</summary>
